info.name: Dum Ka Chicken
info.description: Hyderabadi Style Shahi Dum Ka Murgh is an amazingly delicious, mildly spicy, aromatic and flavoursome main course chicken recipe. In this recipe, well marinated chicken pieces are slow cooked in rich and creamy nut based smooth gravy. Pair this Dum ka Chicken with any Indian bread like Tandoor roti, butter naan or rumali or you can even serve this with Mandi Rice, biryani etc.

info.name: Falafel Shawarma
info.description: Savor the bold flavors of our Falafel Shawarma, where crispy, golden-brown falafel meets warm, soft rumali roti. Stuffed with fresh veggies and drizzled with a zesty tahini sauce, this vibrant dish offers a delightful twist on traditional shawarma, perfect for vegetarians and flavor enthusiasts alike.

info.name: Falafel Bullets- 5 Pieces

info.name: Arabian Meal

info.name: Dil Pasand
info.description: Dil pasand is an famous Indian tutti frutti pie made with homemade puff pastry and tutti frutti (candied papaya) and dry coconut filling.

info.name: Qubani Ka Meetha
info.description: They say that no Hyderabadi meal is complete without tasting the quintessential Hyderabadi dessert, Khubani ka Meetha. Served  Plain, Loaded with Malai or Ice Cream.

info.name: Caramel Pudding
info.description: Caramel Pudding or Flan is a melt in mouth, yummy pudding made by caramelizing sugar, baking it with egg & vanilla and then refrigerating it. Caramel pudding is a treat for sweet lovers and especially kids.
